                    <span>There are a few good ideas in some of the articles, but this book (as well as volume 2)is mostly just about being politically correct in the classroom. Each article is virtually the same thing, with a change of topic. A teacher describes some "issue" they faced in their classroom, describes how they handled it in a pc way and then tells how all the students and parents loved it and concludes by congratulating themself on what a great teacher they are.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Education</div>
